{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10c8a2da-ccaa-453e-bd1d-48774ef691d7","content":"Use `dotnet test --hot-reload` — it watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically. Since your project uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (via `global.json`), this is supported out of the box.\n\nRun:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hot-reload\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. Build and run your tests initially\n2. Watch for source file changes\n3. Automatically re-run affected tests on save\n\nYou can also filter to just your failing test:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hot-reload --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nNo additional packages or configuration needed — your project already has everything required (MSTest 3.8+ and Microsoft.Testing.Platform).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"01d43108-be03-4847-8bc6-d3b1bb07db4e","outputTokens":174,"requestId":"4812:3395C8:8E2C16:A3A4DB:69FBED38"},"id":"783a568d-fc15-467d-a1b1-257ae5e71b68","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:39:08.938Z","parentId":"faa31fa6-bdd4-4d16-86cc-b5363a3a48f6"}
